full_text:
Despite of criticism, CPS decided to go on with SBB in April during the pandemic by claiming that SBB is the most equitable funding forumula.
CPS this year lost 14,500 students from the previous year, which is the sharpest decline in two decades. (6)
full_text(utf-8): b'Despite of criticism, CPS decided to go on with SBB in April during the pandemic by claiming that SBB is the most equitable funding forumula.\nCPS this year lost 14,500 students from the previous year, which is the sharpest decline in two decades. (6)'

full_text: The trend will be spurred as long as SBB formula stays -underenrolled schools will face even more drop in enrollment, while over enrolled school will have overcrowdedness problem in order to maintain those programs. (5)
full_text(utf-8): b'The trend will be spurred as long as SBB formula stays -underenrolled schools will face even more drop in enrollment, while over enrolled school will have overcrowdedness problem in order to maintain those programs. (5)'

full_text: A natural consequence is that parents want to have their kids enroll in well resourced schls, instead of schls in your hood that are stripped of programs and services, through "school choice" system, such as selective enrollment and magnet, or even by moving their address. (4)
full_text(utf-8): b'A natural consequence is that parents want to have their kids enroll in well resourced schls, instead of schls in your hood that are stripped of programs and services, through "school choice" system, such as selective enrollment and magnet, or even by moving their address. (4)'

full_text: For example, if a school is underenrolled, the school will receive less budget, which leads to cuts in staff and programs, such as art, music, library, etc. On the other hand, if another school is fully or overenrolled, the school will receive money to keep those programs. (3)
full_text(utf-8): b'For example, if a school is underenrolled, the school will receive less budget, which leads to cuts in staff and programs, such as art, music, library, etc. On the other hand, if another school is fully or overenrolled, the school will receive money to keep those programs. (3)'

full_text: It has been pointed out that SBB widens the gap between the resourced schools and the underresourced schools and negatively impacts on schools in Black and Brown neighborhoods which have been struggling with chronic underinvestment. (2)

full_text: ユーミンは好きだった。好きな曲、特に荒井時代のが沢山ある。でも私の世代が大学に入る頃にはとっくにバブルは弾けていたので、彼女のバブル満載の世界観はいつも浮世離れしていたし実際ちょっと古くもあった。隣のおしゃれなお姉さんの絵本だけのお話。今回の件は残念だが驚かない。でもやはり残念。

full_text: d) It says attendance will be tracked, but I wonder what is SY20-21 SQRP policy? As parents voiced in @ILRaiseYourHand survey, a moratorium on punitive attendance practice should be in place. Students and teachers need to be able to stay home w/out a symptom, nor Dr's note.

full_text: c) Are 42,000 hand sanitizer dispensers filled with hand sanitizer? 40,000 containers of disinfectant wipes is nice! but there are 600 schools in CPS system. Meaning, each school will receive 66 containers of wipes. About 10 or so containers per grade. Would it be really enough?

full_text: We want to talk about school ratings, but isn't a fundamental question that we have to tackle with how resources are distributed? Otherwise, ratings are very likely to be mere reflections of inequitable funding among schools.
full_text(utf-8): b"We want to talk about school ratings, but isn't a fundamental question that we have to tackle with how resources are distributed? Otherwise, ratings are very likely to be mere reflections of inequitable funding among schools."

full_text: This surprisingly egalitarian public education system was established after WWII under the guidance of the U.S. Of course super-centralization has its own problems, however, in terms of fair distribution of resources, I got to say it works way better than the current U.S. system.
full_text(utf-8): b'This surprisingly egalitarian public education system was established after WWII under the guidance of the U.S. Of course super-centralization has its own problems, however, in terms of fair distribution of resources, I got to say it works way better than the current U.S. system.'

full_text: There is no public school rating system in Japan. All public schools are supposed to be equal, and indeed pretty much they are, due to a) strong central control on curriculums and b) public school funding not relying on property tax. There's no point rating and ranking schools.

full_text: 反レイシズムでは、反レイシズム内からの批判を（尤もなものもそうでないものも）、「敵に塩を送るな」的な一喝で済ませていた人が、山本太郎については見事に敵に塩を送り続けて、その矛盾を省みることはない様子。彼が原発推進派からどんなにひどい誹謗中傷を受けているか知らない訳はあるまいに。

full_text: 派生して。選挙中はいかに反自民票を集結させるかという喫緊の目標があった。立場の似た二人の当落上候補がいた場合、自分の支援する方に少しでも票を集めようとするのは当然だと思う。そして二人とも当選した。もともと立場が近い二人であれば、今後は連携を固くしていかなければならないだろう。

full_text: RT @kama38: 政府の健康被害がないというのは「すぐにない」「後になって出ても証拠がない」という意味。内部被曝の症状は晩発性、一定の時間が経ってから出てくる。白血病とかがんとか、免疫低下とか、でもその時には証明しようがないということ。
